name: Warung Lesehan Bu Mangku
address: Jl. Pantai Saba, Saba, Kec. Blahbatuh, Kabupaten Gianyar, Bali 80581, Indonesia
review 1: A very good value for money restaurant. It has a lot of packages with delicious dishes such as Sate Lilit, fish balls, fish soup. You can also choose to sit in one of their gazebos. Next time you passed Jl. Prof. Ida Bagus Mantra, give it a try!
review 2:
There is many good reviews but I'm not sure why. Food was tastless especially the grilled fish, it waan't fresh and was supposed to be jumbo size but it was very small. Veges and sate sticks was cold I think from the fridge and not fresshly cooked. As for the ice tea all tasted artificial.
Not recommended.
review 3: We live nearby and we love what they do with fish and Balinese traditional dish. They also have fresh coconut for $1. It‚Äôs really good and won‚Äôt break your bank to eat lunch or dinner üòÅ Also really close to Tegenungan waterfall, Saba beach, & Bali Safari.
review 5: Really bad. The food had no Taste. Dont go there

name: Waroeng Billy's 69 Resto
address: 98V9+GCJ, Jl. Prof. Dr. Ida Bagus Mantra, Saba, Kec. Blahbatuh, Kabupaten Gianyar, Bali 80581, Indonesia
review 1: Wow going here in the rainy day had not much expectation, but got super yummy fish - Bali cuisine (perfect combination of spices) with vegetables and very cozy nice atmosphere, good service - highly recommended üåª
review 2: My favourite place to eat ayam / bebek betutu. We come here at least 3 times a month for it. The garden is well maintained, it is a pleasant place to unwind. The staff is always friendly and cheerful.
review 3: Ordered the Mee Soto, Gurame Bakar and Nasi Goreng Ayam. Price was good and food were fresh and tasted great too!!! Recommend for a stopover on the way to Sideman :)
review 4:
The best driver in Bali save & priendly
New car experience Driver
review 5: The food was good. I order mujair bakar & mujair nyanyat, the taste was okay. The place pretty good with some photo spot.

name: Harum Manis Eatery & Lounge
address: Jl. Pantai Saba, Saba, Kec. Blahbatuh, Kabupaten Gianyar, Bali 80581, Indonesia
review 1:
Beautifully designed place, great food and very reasonably priced.
Came here for brekkie and back again for dinner, left feeling happy each time.
Service was good, and the back dining area is gorgeous with rice field view and beautiful lightingüòç
The babur ayam was our favourite dish with great flavours!
We‚Äôll be back when in the area.
review 2:
Developing into a great resto. A new and very nice garden joglo has just been built with rice and coconut tree views. Pleasant atmosphere and positioned just off the bypass plus opposite the hospital make it a great spot.
Menu is varied and quality matches price but at a middle level, not fancy.
Garden is very good just to stop off for a cold drink and rest a while.
review 3:
We ordered take-aways, a grilled chicken and a spaghetti bolognese. The grilled chicken was okay, but I only managed to have one small bite of the spaghetti. It was way over-cooked and too sweet ( like sugar sweet) Tasted something like they put a bottle of cheap instant tomato sauce into it.

Anyway, I should have gone for just the indonesian food. Avoid the western foodü•≤
review 4: The food was okay. Bit expensive compared to other local restaurants in Bali. Mostly targeting tourists.  If you are going with a guide, their commissions will be indirectly added to customers. Taste was not bad. The ambiance was good. But it depends on the seat availability.
review 5:
The first times we went there the food was good, but the last 2 times we ate there it was so bad, they not even know how to make Nasi Goreng with fried egg, we waited 25 Minutes and than was cold, no fried egg. Since the big lady in the kitchen cook the food quality so bad. Last time had Spaghetti Bolognese used to be so good, now make with hot sauce. Sorry never again eat at this place again, better order across at the restaurant at the hospital, great food.
How can a place from good change to so bad.

name: warung muslim sederhana
address: Jl. Prof. Dr. Ida Bagus Mantra No.231, Saba, Kec. Blahbatuh, Kabupaten Gianyar, Bali 80581, Indonesia
review 1: A small restaurant but served you with many variant of indonesia traditional food. The taste are all great and very cheap for me as a tourist. The portion of the food fits me . Not too much not less. If u drive from blah singa waterfall and find a cheap warung for lunch . I suggest you this place.
review 2: Nice food with large variety. 20k for multiple dishes with rice. Came at 4pm once and most food was sold out. Not a great atmosphere but food made up for it.
review 3:
Very good variety of food! Taste and cheap.

Also the people here are soo friendly!
They open until late every day!! üëÄ
review 4: The absolute best food I've tried in many many local Warungs throughout Bali. Also very cheap price
review 5: Delicious, simple, good and cheap. Just a bit noisy, as it is on the main road. Still, I went there several times, cause it was delicious.

name: Coffee Cafe Saba
address: Jl. Pantai Saba No.9, Saba, Kec. Blahbatuh, Kabupaten Gianyar, Bali 80581, Indonesia
review 1: Coffee Cafe Saba is amazing! The staff are so friendly and provide great service, plus the food and drinks are delicious üòç
review 2: You will get a variety of dishes for fair prices. Some of them are convince products for catering and servered as on the menu card. Agreeable Ambiente.j
review 4: Great food selection at ridiculously low prices. We have come to eat here many times now, even when we didn't need a visit to the Hospital.
review 5: For a hospital cafe, it‚Äôs very nice.

review 1: Very popular in Bali. An option if you are looking for fast fried chicken.  That time i was there, many things in the menu were not available. I asked for silver ware but they told they didn't have any. Well, hands was the call. Food flavor acceptable.
review 2:
Eat at a real Warung.
If you want chicken. This is a mediocre choice anything else on the menu is just bad. The sandwiches are empty and greasy. Just go to a locally owned warung. I can suggest a few for you if you like.
review 3: Super cheap tasty geprek! The sambal is not pure spicy like others‚Äô commercialized geprek/penyet joint.

review 1: Located right next to the main street,which is very busy..the rice fields next to the warung gives you different,yet nice feeling and atmosphere,as if you are away from the business of the street..the price is very reasonable and the food is delicious..the staff is very friendly and helpful..there is also a sweet dog guarding the warung..this place is a nice stop when you are on the way through the sanur bypass street..

address: Obaya Rice Bowl, Seberang RS Kasih Ibu, Jl. Pantai Saba, Saba, Kec. Blahbatuh, Bali, 80581, Indonesia
review 1: Oposite to the GH it is a very nice warung with a small garden place you can sit having a nice view on fields. The meals are very tasty, fresh made everything. The service is really well organized and people can speak english quite well, too. Hygienic conditions are good and all is cleaned. For me top!
review 2:
We were in the Hospital nearby and it was an amazing discovery because the food was so delicious and the place very nice.
Highly recommended!!!
review 3:
Amazing experience! The food is really delicious and tasty!
The sambal (spicy sauce) exceptional. If you are looking for the best Japanese restaurant in Bali, this is it!
